  <summary>9/17/1997--Introduced.
Career Transition Assistance Act of 1997 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) exclude from gross income a limited amount of qualified severance pay; and (2) permit a limited credit for qualified job training expenses for certain individuals over the age of 50 who have been laid off.</summary>
